21
00:01:59,000 --> 00:02:04,000
But they don't fall down off the planet because gravity doesn't actually pull them down.

22
00:02:04,000 --> 00:02:07,000
Down is an illusion of your reference frame.

23
00:02:07,000 --> 00:02:11,000
To Earth's reference frame, gravity just pulls in.

24
00:02:11,000 --> 00:02:17,000
But for humans, there is an up and down, because within our frame of reference, that just makes sense.

25
00:02:17,000 --> 00:02:24,000
Which is also why we think that the planet itself has an up and down, north and south, and we made our maps accordingly.

26
00:02:24,000 --> 00:02:29,000
But an observer looking at the solar system might disagree.

27
00:02:29,000 --> 00:02:34,000
Our maps make sense to us because we're used to them, not because they are correct.

28
00:02:34,000 --> 00:02:41,000
Okay, so this is step one. Your position on what feels like a flat surface, but is actually a sphere.

29
